# Click Platform - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Structure

- `client/` - Next.js 14 frontend (React, TypeScript, Tailwind)
- `server/` - Express backend (Node.js, Mongoose)
- `prisma/` - Database schema

## Code Style

- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Prefer const/let over var
- Use async/await over callbacks
- Follow existing patterns in the file you're editing

## Key Files

- ROADMAP_STATUS.md - Current work status, next stages
- ROADMAP_WORKFLOW_GUIDE.md - Collaboration workflow
- COLLABORATION_GUIDE.md - Git + PR workflow

## Conventions

- API routes: server/routes/
- Services: server/services/
- React components: client/components/
- Use client/lib/api.ts for API calls
- Check server/middleware/auth.js for auth patterns

## When Making Changes

- Create feature branches, not direct commits to main
- One logical change per PR
- Update ROADMAP_STATUS.md when completing roadmap items
